==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*beugan''.  Cognate with Old Saxon ''[[bugan#Old Saxon|būgan]]'' (Dutch ''[[buigen]]''), Old High German ''[[biogan]]'' (German ''[[biegen]]''), Gothic [[𐌱𐌹𐌿𐌲𐌰𐌽]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈbu:ɣɑn/}}

===Verb===
{{Latinx|'''būgan'''}} (class II strong: ''3 singular preterite'' '''[[beah|bēah]]''', ''preterite plural'' '''[[bugon]]''', ''past participle'' '''[[bogen]]''')

# to [[bend]], [[bow]] (down)
# to turn away, [[withdraw]]

===Descendants===
*English: [[bow]]

